01:39:09,200 --> 01:39:10,680
Ms. G?

1411
01:39:11,040 --> 01:39:13,280
Are we gonna have
this same room next year, again?

1412
01:39:13,360 --> 01:39:16,360
I don't know.
You're gonna be juniors next year.

1413
01:39:17,840 --> 01:39:19,320
What do you mean?

1414
01:39:19,400 --> 01:39:22,000
Well, I teach freshman
and sophomore years.

1415
01:39:22,120 --> 01:39:25,120
You mean,
we're not gonna be with you next year?

1416
01:39:27,720 --> 01:39:29,000
Well, I...

1417
01:39:30,800 --> 01:39:34,400
I don't teach juniors.
I thought you guys understood that.

1418
01:39:34,880 --> 01:39:35,960
What? What are you talking about?

1419
01:39:38,080 --> 01:39:39,640
You don't wanna be our teacher
next year?

1420
01:39:39,720 --> 01:39:42,160
Of course I do. I can't.

1421
01:39:42,280 --> 01:39:44,640
- Why not?
- It's the Board of Ed.

1422
01:39:44,760 --> 01:39:46,600
It's regulations.

1423
01:39:49,240 --> 01:39:51,920
Ms. G hasn't been here long enough
to have seniority.

1424
01:39:51,960 --> 01:39:53,240
Who cares about seniority?

1425
01:39:53,360 --> 01:39:55,840
Shit! They can't do that!
They don't have the right!

1426
01:39:57,840 --> 01:40:00,520
- Ms. G, this is our kick-it spot.
- Yeah.

1427
01:40:00,680 --> 01:40:03,960
Everybody's cool with everybody.
Everybody knows everybody.

1428
01:40:04,080 --> 01:40:07,400
This is the only place
where we really get to be ourselves.

1429
01:40:07,520 --> 01:40:09,440
There's no place like this
out there for us.

1430
01:40:09,720 --> 01:40:11,040
That's true.

1431
01:40:11,560 --> 01:40:14,000
I'm not allowed
to teach junior and seniors.

1432
01:40:14,120 --> 01:40:15,080
You're not allowed?

1433
01:40:17,000 --> 01:40:20,480
Ms. G, we can fight this, you know,
like the Freedom Riders.

1434
01:40:20,600 --> 01:40:22,280
Yeah, yeah,
we'll all drive around on a bus.

1435
01:40:22,400 --> 01:40:24,280
Only this time, they try and bust us up,

1436
01:40:24,400 --> 01:40:26,120
We bust a few of them
board members' heads.

1437
01:40:26,760 --> 01:40:27,680
Marcus.

1438
01:40:27,800 --> 01:40:31,280
Or we can go to the newspapers,
media. That'll get their attention.

1439
01:40:31,520 --> 01:40:32,920
Or we can paint
the administration building

1440
01:40:33,040 --> 01:40:35,400
With the word "assholes"
in various colors.

1441
01:40:37,080 --> 01:40:38,720
Hey, it's something. We can do this.

1442
01:40:43,920 --> 01:40:44,840
What?

1443
01:40:44,960 --> 01:40:48,360
These are my books, not Scott's.
I'm packing the wrong books.

1444
01:40:48,480 --> 01:40:50,080
Honey, take a break.

1445
01:40:53,880 --> 01:40:55,280
Sit down.

1446
01:40:58,320 --> 01:41:00,800
I can't believe I'm getting divorced.

1447
01:41:02,240 --> 01:41:04,560
I never thought this would happen.

1448
01:41:08,360 --> 01:41:10,400
What do I do now?

1449
01:41:11,320 --> 01:41:13,680
Next year, I won't even have my kids.

1450
01:41:14,080 --> 01:41:16,280
You think you should stay with them?

1451
01:41:17,120 --> 01:41:19,320
Or is it better they move on?

1452
01:41:19,640 --> 01:41:21,040
I don't know.

1453
01:41:24,680 --> 01:41:27,080
It's just a job, like you said.

1454
01:41:27,160 --> 01:41:28,720
Yeah, it is.

1455
01:41:29,640 --> 01:41:31,520
But is the job finished?

1456
01:41:33,760 --> 01:41:35,280
Listen to me now.

1457
01:41:35,560 --> 01:41:37,960
What you've done with those kids...

1458
01:41:40,280 --> 01:41:42,480
I don't even have words for it.

1459
01:41:44,160 --> 01:41:48,920
But one thing's for sure,
you are an amazing teacher.

1460
01:41:50,720 --> 01:41:52,000
Special.

1461
01:41:52,760 --> 01:41:57,000
You have been blessed with a burden,
my daughter.

1462
01:41:58,880 --> 01:42:00,760
And I envy you that.

1463
01:42:03,360 --> 01:42:04,920
And I admire you.

1464
01:42:07,320 --> 01:42:11,160
And how many fathers ever get
to say that to their daughters

1465
01:42:11,280 --> 01:42:13,160
And really mean it?

1466
01:42:16,880 --> 01:42:19,840
What she is suggesting
is in violation of our union charter.

1467
01:42:19,960 --> 01:42:23,000
She may not move on with her students
to teach them junior year.

1468
01:42:23,080 --> 01:42:25,000
She's only been here two years.

1469
01:42:25,120 --> 01:42:27,120
There are teachers here
who have tenure,

1470
01:42:27,240 --> 01:42:29,400
Who have worked and committed
themselves for far longer

1471
01:42:29,480 --> 01:42:31,320
To attain a position of seniority.

1472
01:42:31,400 --> 01:42:35,200
Not to mention their experience
in teaching students of a higher caliber.

1473
01:42:35,320 --> 01:42:38,000
The Distinguished Scholars Program
is under our jurisdiction.

1474
01:42:38,160 --> 01:42:40,800
I don't want to replace
the Distinguished Scholars Program.

1475
01:42:40,960 --> 01:42:42,760
I just want to stay
with my kids next year.

1476
01:42:42,880 --> 01:42:44,960
She can't. I have the juniors.

1477
01:42:45,040 --> 01:42:47,000
The Board of Education
will not allow this.

1478
01:42:47,120 --> 01:42:48,960
Teaching rotations will be disrupted,

1479
01:42:49,080 --> 01:42:51,280
Retirement schedules
will be reevaluated,

1480
01:42:51,400 --> 01:42:54,680
Disrespecting teachers
who have earned their way far longer

1481
01:42:54,760 --> 01:42:56,840
And who focus on the classroom,

1482
01:42:56,960 --> 01:42:59,680
Not on public relations
and newspaper articles.

1483
01:42:59,760 --> 01:43:01,680
I didn't ask for those articles
to be written.

1484
01:43:01,800 --> 01:43:03,200
She's in the middle of a divorce.

1485
01:43:03,320 --> 01:43:05,720
Note, they stay late in her class,
they're eating, they're playing games!

1486
01:43:05,800 --> 01:43:08,800
All right, let's all just take a breath here.
All right?

1487
01:43:10,160 --> 01:43:12,160
Now I had hoped
that we could talk this out,

1488
01:43:12,320 --> 01:43:13,920
Maybe come to some kind
of arrangement.

1489
01:43:14,080 --> 01:43:16,440
- There is no arrangement...
- Margaret.

1490
01:43:17,280 --> 01:43:18,680
Carl, look.

1491
01:43:19,240 --> 01:43:22,200
Putting aside all obvious resentments
for the moment,

1492
01:43:22,280 --> 01:43:23,640
Even if an arrangement were made

1493
01:43:23,720 --> 01:43:27,680
And she could teach them as juniors,
there isn't an accredited course

1494
01:43:27,800 --> 01:43:30,080
In the curriculum for her to teach.

1495
01:43:30,680 --> 01:43:34,200
Unless Brian trades one of his
junior classes for a sophomore.

1496
01:43:34,280 --> 01:43:35,320
No.

1497
01:43:37,000 --> 01:43:39,160
Then there's nothing I can do.

1498
01:43:42,560 --> 01:43:43,800
So that's it?

1499
01:43:44,880 --> 01:43:46,280
Believe it or not, Ms. Gruwell,

1500
01:43:46,400 --> 01:43:49,000
There are other capable teachers
in this school.

1501
01:43:49,160 --> 01:43:51,040
If you've made the progress
you say you have,

1502
01:43:51,200 --> 01:43:52,800
Your students should be ready
to move on.

1503
01:43:52,880 --> 01:43:55,440
They might even gain something
from more experienced teachers.

1504
01:43:55,560 --> 01:43:58,680
You can't teach them.
You don't even like them.

1505
01:43:58,760 --> 01:44:00,520
What does that have to do
with teaching?

1506
01:44:00,640 --> 01:44:03,120
I've been an educator for over 30 years.

1507
01:44:03,520 --> 01:44:05,120
I have students that still remain
in touch with me.

1508
01:44:05,240 --> 01:44:07,560
I know what it is to be loved
by a classroom!

1509
01:44:07,680 --> 01:44:10,520
You have no idea
how many battles I've had

1510
01:44:10,600 --> 01:44:12,200
Fighting to be a better teacher,

1511
01:44:12,320 --> 01:44:15,520
And now, what, suddenly I'm incapable
of educating your students?

1512
01:44:15,640 --> 01:44:18,200
You know, if they move on
to our classes and they fail,

1513
01:44:18,320 --> 01:44:20,280
It'll be because they weren't prepared!

1514
01:44:20,440 --> 01:44:23,040
Lt'll be because you failed, not them!

1515
01:44:40,840 --> 01:44:43,400
Andre? Wait a minute before you go in.

1516
01:44:56,120 --> 01:44:58,480
I heard about your brother's conviction.
I'm sorry.

1517
01:44:58,600 --> 01:45:00,720
Is that why you've missed class
so much?

1518
01:45:00,840 --> 01:45:02,560
I had things to do.

1519
01:45:05,680 --> 01:45:07,400
About this.

1520
01:45:07,880 --> 01:45:08,960
The evaluation assignment

1521
01:45:09,080 --> 01:45:10,480
Was to grade yourself
on the work you're doing.

1522
01:45:10,600 --> 01:45:12,920
You gave yourself an F.
What's that about?

1523
01:45:13,320 --> 01:45:16,360
- It's what I feel I deserve. That's all.
- Oh, really?

1524
01:45:17,880 --> 01:45:19,520
You know what this is?

1525
01:45:19,800 --> 01:45:23,640
This is a "Fuck you" to me,
and everyone in this class!

1526
01:45:23,760 --> 01:45:26,880
I don't want excuses.
I know what you're up against.

1527
01:45:27,240 --> 01:45:29,360
We're all of us up against something.

1528
01:45:30,280 --> 01:45:33,520
So you better make up your mind,
because until you have the balls

1529
01:45:33,640 --> 01:45:36,320
To look me straight in the eye
and tell me this is all you deserve,

1530
01:45:36,400 --> 01:45:37,880
I am not letting you fail,

1531
01:45:37,960 --> 01:45:39,920
Even if that means coming
to your house every night

1532
01:45:40,040 --> 01:45:41,640
Until you finish the work.

1533
01:45:41,760 --> 01:45:43,480
I see who you are.

1534
01:45:44,000 --> 01:45:46,040
Do you understand me?

1535
01:45:47,000 --> 01:45:48,880
I can see you.

1536
01:45:50,680 --> 01:45:52,520
And you are not failing.

1537
01:45:55,840 --> 01:46:00,560
So, take a minute.
Pull yourself together and come inside.

1538
01:46:01,080 --> 01:46:03,000
I want a new evaluation.

1539
01:46:08,040 --> 01:46:10,720
An F. What, are you tripping?

1540
01:46:16,160 --> 01:46:19,480
I want you all to know that
Dr. Cohn and I tried very hard.

1541
01:46:22,120 --> 01:46:24,880
But it's been decided we can't continue
with each other junior year.

1542
01:46:25,000 --> 01:46:26,080
- What?
- What?

1543
01:46:27,640 --> 01:46:29,440
You... Wait.

1544
01:46:30,160 --> 01:46:32,040
Wait. Guys. Everyone.

1545
01:46:33,400 --> 01:46:35,760
No! That don't fly, Ma!

1546
01:46:37,280 --> 01:46:40,800
Look, first of all,
I'm not anyone's mother in here, okay?

1547
01:46:40,880 --> 01:46:43,000
No, it doesn't mean mother.

1548
01:46:43,680 --> 01:46:45,920
It's a sign of respect for you.

1549
01:46:59,560 --> 01:47:00,880
Listen to me.

1550
01:47:01,120 --> 01:47:02,360
All of you.

1551
01:47:03,080 --> 01:47:07,520
Don't use me as another excuse
for why you can't make it.

1552
01:47:09,360 --> 01:47:12,520
You made it to your junior year.

1553
01:47:13,320 --> 01:47:16,000
Think about how you did that.

1554
01:47:17,320 --> 01:47:20,800
Everyone in this room
has a chance to graduate.

1555
01:47:21,800 --> 01:47:24,280
For some,
you'll be the first in your family.

1556
01:47:24,360 --> 01:47:27,040
The first with a choice to go to college.

1557
01:47:28,000 --> 01:47:30,680
Some may move faster than others.

1558
01:47:32,200 --> 01:47:34,400
But you'll each have the chance.

1559
01:47:35,440 --> 01:47:38,280
And you did that. Not me.

1560
01:47:45,080 --> 01:47:48,600
Now, I have one

1561
01:47:50,560 --> 01:47:52,080
Final project in mind.

1562
01:47:52,200 --> 01:47:54,280
- Ms. G.
- Yeah?

1563
01:47:56,040 --> 01:48:00,800
<i>Ms. G wanted us to put our diaries
together in a book, just like Anne Frank.</i>

1564
01:48:01,520 --> 01:48:03,480
<i>She got this businessman, John Tu,</i>

1565
01:48:03,600 --> 01:48:06,320
<i>to donate 35 computers
so we could work.</i>

1566
01:48:11,200 --> 01:48:14,440
<i>She told us we have something
to say to people.</i>

1567
01:48:14,600 --> 01:48:15,760
<i>We weren't just kids
in a class anymore.</i>

1568
01:48:15,800 --> 01:48:16,920
<i>We weren't just kids
in a class anymore.</i>

1569
01:48:17,000 --> 01:48:20,560
<i>We were writers with our own voices,
our own stories.</i>

1570
01:48:20,680 --> 01:48:22,640
<i>And even if nobody else read it,</i>

1571
01:48:22,760 --> 01:48:26,200
<i>the book would be something
to leave behind that said we were here,</i>

1572
01:48:26,760 --> 01:48:29,760
<i>this is what happened, we mattered.</i>

1573
01:48:30,200 --> 01:48:34,280
<i>Even if it was just to each other.
And we won't forget.</i>

1574
01:48:35,920 --> 01:48:38,200
<i>Ms. G didn't promise
it would get published or anything,</i>

1575
01:48:38,280 --> 01:48:41,040
<i>but we could get it out there ourselves.</i>

1576
01:48:41,760 --> 01:48:43,880
<i>She asked us to come up with a title,</i>

1577
01:48:44,400 --> 01:48:46,280
<i>something to call ourselves.</i>

1578
01:49:03,360 --> 01:49:05,120
I just received a call
from Karin Polacheck

1579
01:49:05,280 --> 01:49:06,320
At the Board of Education.

1580
01:49:06,440 --> 01:49:08,360
There's to be a meeting
with Dr. Cohn about your classes.

1581
01:49:08,520 --> 01:49:11,800
- Do you know anything about this?
- No.

1582
01:49:19,280 --> 01:49:24,520
These students, this class,
they've become a family.

1583
01:49:25,400 --> 01:49:26,920
To who? To you?

1584
01:49:27,560 --> 01:49:29,120
To each other.

1585
01:49:29,920 --> 01:49:33,120
Room 203 is a kind of a home for them.

1586
01:49:33,640 --> 01:49:36,800
Their trust is all wrapped up
in us being together as a group.

1587
01:49:37,240 --> 01:49:38,320
Once they're out of her class,

1588
01:49:38,440 --> 01:49:40,800
Believe me they'll slip back
into their old habits.

1589
01:49:40,880 --> 01:49:44,680
Their reading scores, their writing
has markedly improved, Ms. Campbell.

1590
01:49:44,840 --> 01:49:48,160
On paper. But what has
she accomplished in reality?

1591
01:49:48,280 --> 01:49:49,840
What about new students
that come in next year?

1592
01:49:49,960 --> 01:49:51,840
Can she repeat
this process every year?

1593
01:49:51,960 --> 01:49:53,280
Her methods are impractical,

1594
01:49:53,400 --> 01:49:55,920
Impossible to implement with regularity.

1595
01:49:56,040 --> 01:49:58,400
What if every teacher
performed in this way?

1596
01:49:59,000 --> 01:50:00,160
We have millions of children

1597
01:50:00,280 --> 01:50:01,920
To get through the education system
in this country,

1598
01:50:02,040 --> 01:50:03,800
And we need a means
of accomplishing that

1599
01:50:03,880 --> 01:50:06,680
Which allows as many students
to benefit as possible,

1600
01:50:06,760 --> 01:50:08,640
Not just special cases.

1601
01:50:10,080 --> 01:50:13,400
And you honestly think you can create
this family in every classroom,

1602
01:50:13,520 --> 01:50:16,360
For every grade,
for every student you teach?

1603
01:50:20,760 --> 01:50:22,160
I don't know.

1604
01:50:28,120 --> 01:50:29,400
Thank you.

1605
01:50:48,960 --> 01:50:51,720
Hey, there go Ms. G.
Hey, there go Ms. G!

1606
01:51:00,280 --> 01:51:01,600
What happened?

1607
01:51:02,400 --> 01:51:06,040
So? Are we gonna be together
for junior year?

1608
01:51:11,640 --> 01:51:12,880
No.

1609
01:51:13,800 --> 01:51:15,560
- What?
- What?

1610
01:51:20,000 --> 01:51:23,200
We're gonna be together junior
and senior year.

1611
01:51:24,600 --> 01:51:25,600
Yes!

1612
01:51:28,240 --> 01:51:30,080
I can't get involved
in inner school policy.

1613
01:51:30,160 --> 01:51:32,280
My principal only listens
to my department head,

1614
01:51:32,440 --> 01:51:34,320
And she's not very supportive.

1615
01:51:34,400 --> 01:51:36,080
You'll have to find a way to deal with it.

1616
01:51:36,160 --> 01:51:38,840
No, I'd rather just deal directly
with someone in power.

1617
01:51:38,960 --> 01:51:41,000
Ms. Gruwell, there's a system in place

1618
01:51:41,120 --> 01:51:43,800
Based on years of running
an educational facility.

1619
01:51:44,000 --> 01:51:46,960
- You have to follow that system.
- No. I won't.

1620
01:51:47,920 --> 01:51:50,760
Look, I'm just trying to do my job here.

1621
01:51:50,840 --> 01:51:53,640
What's the point
of a voluntary integration program

1622
01:51:53,720 --> 01:51:56,400
If the kids making it to high school
have a 5th grade reading level?

1623
01:51:56,520 --> 01:51:58,240
I enforced that program.

1624
01:51:58,320 --> 01:51:59,400
With all due respect,

1625
01:51:59,480 --> 01:52:01,760
All that program is doing
is warehousing these kids

1626
01:52:01,920 --> 01:52:03,240
Until they're old enough to disappear.

1627
01:52:03,320 --> 01:52:04,880
Look, I appreciate your intentions,

1628
01:52:05,040 --> 01:52:07,520
But there's nothing I can do
on a class-by-class basis.

1629
01:52:07,600 --> 01:52:11,000
Dr. Cohn, why should they waste
their time showing up

1630
01:52:11,120 --> 01:52:13,720
When they know
we're wasting our time teaching them?

1631
01:52:13,800 --> 01:52:16,400
We tell them, "Go to school.
Get an education. "

1632
01:52:16,520 --> 01:52:20,480
And then we say, "Well, they can't learn,
so let's not waste resources. "

1633
01:52:20,800 --> 01:52:22,240
I'm thinking trips.

1634
01:52:22,360 --> 01:52:25,120
Most of them have never
been outside of Long Beach.

1635
01:52:25,200 --> 01:52:27,560
They haven't been given the opportunity

1636
01:52:27,680 --> 01:52:30,080
To expand their thinking
about what's out there for them.

1637
01:52:30,160 --> 01:52:31,520
And they're hungry for it. I know it.

1638
01:52:31,640 --> 01:52:33,680
And it's purely a reward system.

1639
01:52:33,800 --> 01:52:35,520
They won't get anything
they haven't earned

1640
01:52:35,640 --> 01:52:37,640
By doing their work
and upping their grades.

1641
01:52:37,800 --> 01:52:39,040
But if Ms. Campbell
won't give you books

1642
01:52:39,160 --> 01:52:40,160
Because of budget restrictions,

1643
01:52:40,320 --> 01:52:41,360
She's not gonna approve school trips.

1644
01:52:41,520 --> 01:52:42,880
I'll raise the money.

1645
01:52:43,000 --> 01:52:45,520
I just need to know
I won't meet resistance.

1646
01:52:45,920 --> 01:52:47,880
See, I can't promise them anything
I can't deliver.

1647
01:52:48,000 --> 01:52:50,360
It only proves what they already believe.

1648
01:52:52,200 --> 01:52:55,880
All I'm saying is, Ms. Campbell
doesn't need to be bothered.

1649
01:52:59,240 --> 01:53:00,960
You're a concierge at the Marriott?

1650
01:53:01,040 --> 01:53:02,120
