I know what I have to say.

2122
02:22:51,160 --> 02:22:52,200
Yeah.

2123
02:22:52,840 --> 02:22:55,000
- You know how that is.
- I know.

2124
02:22:56,320 --> 02:22:58,840
And that man that put your father
in prison,

2125
02:22:58,960 --> 02:23:01,520
He knew he was sending
an innocent man.

2126
02:23:01,880 --> 02:23:03,120
But, you know,

2127
02:23:04,960 --> 02:23:06,480
He was just

2128
02:23:08,480 --> 02:23:10,160
Protecting his own.

2129
02:23:16,120 --> 02:23:18,680
What the hell does everybody
want from me?

2130
02:23:44,400 --> 02:23:46,280
Hey, Mama. Mama.

2131
02:23:51,640 --> 02:23:53,960
What the hell are you doing here?

2132
02:24:00,000 --> 02:24:03,800
I want to come home.
I don't want to be in the streets no more.

2133
02:24:03,880 --> 02:24:05,120
I'm sorry.

2134
02:24:07,520 --> 02:24:10,520
I want to change. I can't do it alone.

2135
02:24:12,360 --> 02:24:13,920
I need you, Mama.

2136
02:24:15,640 --> 02:24:17,080
I need you.

2137
02:24:53,200 --> 02:24:54,880
And what time was that?

2138
02:24:55,720 --> 02:24:57,920
I told you, 9:00, 9:30.

2139
02:24:58,560 --> 02:24:59,960
And you had a clear view
of the defendant,

2140
02:25:00,080 --> 02:25:01,840
Grant Rice, in the store?

2141
02:25:03,000 --> 02:25:05,280
I told you he was playing
the video game.

2142
02:25:05,880 --> 02:25:08,240
Then what happened?
What did you see?

2143
02:25:08,640 --> 02:25:10,640
Well, he got all whacked
because he lost the game,

2144
02:25:10,800 --> 02:25:14,240
And then he started shouting and all,
threatening everybody.

2145
02:25:14,360 --> 02:25:17,400
He threatened everyone?
He threatened you?

2146
02:25:18,480 --> 02:25:20,800
No. The guy who ran the store.

2147
02:25:20,920 --> 02:25:22,880
He wanted his money back
for the game.

2148
02:25:22,920 --> 02:25:24,880
And what did the store owner do?

2149
02:25:25,680 --> 02:25:28,840
He shouted back.
And they were fighting.

2150
02:25:29,080 --> 02:25:33,200
Then he, the defendant, knocked
something over and left the store.

2151
02:25:33,720 --> 02:25:36,120
And then what happened?
What did you see?

2152
02:25:40,120 --> 02:25:41,680
I saw...

2153
02:25:53,400 --> 02:25:54,800
I saw...

2154
02:26:09,440 --> 02:26:10,840
Paco did it.

2155
02:26:14,840 --> 02:26:16,520
Paco killed the guy.

2156
02:27:38,640 --> 02:27:41,040
My father won't talk to me anymore.

2157
02:27:43,320 --> 02:27:48,440
And I have to lay low for a little while
because there's word out to jump me.

2158
02:27:49,800 --> 02:27:52,000
So I'm gonna be living with my aunt.

2159
02:27:53,400 --> 02:27:58,160
See, my aunt lives even further away,

2160
02:28:00,160 --> 02:28:04,280
So I was just wondering if I could, like,

2161
02:28:07,320 --> 02:28:09,000
Stay here late with you

2162
02:28:09,040 --> 02:28:10,720
Stay here late with you

2163
02:28:12,520 --> 02:28:16,840
So I can get my homework done,
'cause it's late by the time I get home.

2164
02:28:19,200 --> 02:28:22,040
You can stay as late as you want.

2165
02:28:23,360 --> 02:28:27,160
And I can even drive you to your aunt's,
if it gets too late.

2166
02:28:30,280 --> 02:28:32,040
Ms. G, let's not get nuts.

2167
02:29:06,360 --> 02:29:08,200
I think I got your color.

2168
02:29:52,960 --> 02:29:54,880
Just come by the concierge
on your way out,

2169
02:29:55,000 --> 02:29:57,640
I'll have the directions for you.
Yep, that's fine.

2170
02:30:04,400 --> 02:30:08,040
Stop! That's it! Now, now! Hey!

2171
02:30:09,720 --> 02:30:12,080
You get an extra three seconds. Go!

