02:30:20,280 --> 02:30:24,360
<i>In 1961, an interracial civil rights group
traveled by bus through the South</i>

2174
02:30:24,440 --> 02:30:26,120
<i>to challenge segregation.</i>

2175
02:30:26,200 --> 02:30:28,960
<i>Blacks sat in the front,
whites in the back.</i>

2176
02:30:29,400 --> 02:30:32,800
<i>They were attacked, firebombed,
but they kept going.</i>

2177
02:30:33,400 --> 02:30:37,360
<i>In Montgomery, Alabama, Jim Zwerg
offered to be the first off the bus,</i>

2178
02:30:37,480 --> 02:30:39,760
<i>knowing there was a mob
waiting for them.</i>

2179
02:30:39,880 --> 02:30:42,720
<i>He was almost beaten to death
so the others could get away.</i>

2180
02:30:42,840 --> 02:30:46,160
<i>That kind of courage
is unbelievable to me.</i>

2181
02:30:46,320 --> 02:30:49,520
<i>I was afraid of just being in this class,
and I was ashamed</i>

2182
02:30:49,640 --> 02:30:53,240
<i>because I've always been the dumb kid
in school, even with my friends.</i>

2183
02:30:53,400 --> 02:30:54,720
<i>But not anymore.</i>

2184
02:30:54,880 --> 02:30:56,360
<i>And I must have some kind of courage,</i>

2185
02:30:56,440 --> 02:31:00,040
<i>because I could have lied
to get out of here, but I stayed.</i>

2186
02:31:01,080 --> 02:31:02,320
<i>I stayed.</i>

2187
02:31:02,720 --> 02:31:03,960
Hi, I'm home!

2188
02:31:04,560 --> 02:31:09,280
Sorry, it got late. I drove the kids home.
I didn't want them taking buses.

2189
02:31:09,800 --> 02:31:12,080
You're never gonna believe
what happened.

2190
02:31:13,400 --> 02:31:14,960
I'm so tired.

2191
02:31:15,480 --> 02:31:18,200
It's so cute, though.
They never want to go home.

2192
02:31:18,840 --> 02:31:21,960
We have such a good time together.
I'm gonna take a shower.

2193
02:31:40,760 --> 02:31:43,760
If you have another glass,
you're gonna have a headache.

2194
02:31:44,480 --> 02:31:48,720
Your bags are packed and you think
the wine's gonna give me a headache?

2195
02:31:50,640 --> 02:31:52,320
Why are you doing this?

2196
02:31:52,440 --> 02:31:55,560
Because I don't
pay enough attention to you?

2197
02:31:55,640 --> 02:31:57,560
No. That's not it.

2198
02:31:59,800 --> 02:32:03,720
I just... I feel like I'm living a life
I just did not agree to.

2199
02:32:05,960 --> 02:32:07,520
Erin, it's just...

2200
02:32:08,720 --> 02:32:10,120
It's too hard.

2201
02:32:10,720 --> 02:32:12,800
Your life is too hard?

2202
02:32:13,280 --> 02:32:15,720
I think what you're doing is noble.

2203
02:32:16,280 --> 02:32:19,720
And it's good. And I'm proud of you.

2204
02:32:20,280 --> 02:32:21,520
I am.

2205
02:32:23,800 --> 02:32:26,960
I just want to live my life
and not feel bad about it.

2206
02:32:27,040 --> 02:32:30,080
- I'm not trying to make you feel bad.
- You don't have to try.

2207
02:32:30,200 --> 02:32:32,880
I didn't plan on becoming responsible
for these kids.

2208
02:32:32,960 --> 02:32:34,920
- Well, who asked you to?
- No one asked me to!

2209
02:32:35,000 --> 02:32:35,960
They're not even your kids!

2210
02:32:36,080 --> 02:32:39,720
Why do I have to be asked? Scott...

2211
02:32:43,680 --> 02:32:48,400
I finally realized what I'm
supposed to be doing and I love it.

2212
02:32:48,520 --> 02:32:53,000
When I'm helping these kids
make sense of their lives,

2213
02:32:53,600 --> 02:32:56,320
Everything about my life
makes sense to me.

2214
02:32:59,720 --> 02:33:02,000
How often does a person get that?

2215
02:33:05,160 --> 02:33:09,080
- Then what do you need me for?
- You're my husband.

2216
02:33:09,200 --> 02:33:13,880
Why can't you stand by me and be part
of it, the way wives support husbands?

2217
02:33:14,000 --> 02:33:15,760
Because I can't be your wife.

2218
02:33:22,800 --> 02:33:25,000
I wish I could make that
sound less awful.

2219
02:33:27,080 --> 02:33:28,200
Erin?

2220
02:33:29,720 --> 02:33:32,200
You know,
if you had to choose between us

2221
02:33:33,640 --> 02:33:35,200
And the class,

2222
02:33:36,920 --> 02:33:38,320
Who would you pick?

2223
02:33:40,280 --> 02:33:43,560
If you love me,
how could you ever ask me that?

2224
02:33:44,520 --> 02:33:46,080
Erin, look at me.

2225
02:33:49,440 --> 02:33:51,520
This is all there's ever been to me.

2226
02:33:51,880 --> 02:33:56,080
This is it. I'm not one of those kids.
I don't have any more potential.

2227
02:33:57,840 --> 02:33:59,280
See? You don't want to be here either,

2228
02:33:59,440 --> 02:34:02,640
'cause if you did, would you be
in the classroom every night?

2229
02:34:03,920 --> 02:34:08,360
That's not true. I want to be here.
I love you.

2230
02:34:09,480 --> 02:34:11,360
You love the idea of me.

2231
02:34:16,680 --> 02:34:18,880
But it's such a great idea.

2232
02:34:22,400 --> 02:34:23,640
I know.

2233
02:34:50,560 --> 02:34:52,280
Dad? Hi.

2234
02:34:54,800 --> 02:34:57,840
You know, I was actually trying
to call someone else,

2235
02:34:58,000 --> 02:34:59,880
And I automatically dialed you. I'm sorry.

2236
02:34:59,920 --> 02:35:02,360
Look, I'm gonna call you tomorrow,
okay?

2237
02:35:02,520 --> 02:35:05,680
I need to make this call. I love you.

2238
02:35:18,200 --> 02:35:20,560
<i>Ms. G made us read Twelve Angry Men.</i>

2239
02:35:20,680 --> 02:35:24,160
<i>It's all about how this one juror
helped to turn the hearts of 11 jurors.</i>

2240
02:35:24,200 --> 02:35:25,960
<i>It made me feel hopeful.</i>

2241
02:35:26,480 --> 02:35:29,600
<i>At 2:00 today, my brother
was given a verdict on his own trial.</i>

2242
02:35:29,720 --> 02:35:32,240
<i>No O. J. Dream Team,
just a court-appointed attorney</i>

2243
02:35:32,400 --> 02:35:34,280
<i>who probably thought
his ass was guilty.</i>

2244
02:35:34,400 --> 02:35:37,880
<i>And I realized Twelve Angry Men
was just a book and nothing more.</i>

2245
02:35:38,200 --> 02:35:40,840
<i>My brother got 15 years to life.</i>

2246
02:35:40,920 --> 02:35:43,560
<i>Justice don't mean
the bad guy goes to jail.</i>

2247
02:35:43,640 --> 02:35:45,760
<i>It just means somebody
pays for the crime.</i>

2248
02:35:51,360 --> 02:35:52,840
So, you got time now?

2249
02:35:59,440 --> 02:36:00,960
Anyone know where Andre's been?

2250
02:36:01,080 --> 02:36:02,320
I haven't seen him on the bus.

2251
02:36:02,440 --> 02:36:03,840
Yeah, I haven't talked to him either.

2252
02:36:12,400 --> 02:36:13,840
Ms. G?

2253
02:36:14,200 --> 02:36:16,440
Are we gonna have
