2255
02:36:21,040 --> 02:36:22,480
What do you mean?

2256
02:36:22,600 --> 02:36:25,200
Well, I teach freshman
and sophomore years.

2257
02:36:25,280 --> 02:36:28,280
You mean,
we're not gonna be with you next year?

2258
02:36:30,880 --> 02:36:32,200
Well, I...

2259
02:36:34,000 --> 02:36:37,560
I don't teach juniors.
I thought you guys understood that.

2260
02:36:38,040 --> 02:36:39,120
What? What are you talking about?

2261
02:36:41,240 --> 02:36:42,800
You don't wanna be our teacher
next year?

2262
02:36:42,920 --> 02:36:45,320
Of course I do. I can't.

2263
02:36:45,440 --> 02:36:47,840
- Why not?
- It's the Board of Ed.

2264
02:36:47,960 --> 02:36:49,800
It's regulations.

2265
02:36:52,440 --> 02:36:55,120
Ms. G hasn't been here long enough
to have seniority.

2266
02:36:55,160 --> 02:36:56,400
Who cares about seniority?

2267
02:36:56,560 --> 02:36:59,000
Shit! They can't do that!
They don't have the right!

2268
02:37:01,040 --> 02:37:03,720
- Ms. G, this is our kick-it spot.
- Yeah.

2269
02:37:03,840 --> 02:37:07,160
Everybody's cool with everybody.
Everybody knows everybody.

2270
02:37:07,280 --> 02:37:10,560
This is the only place
where we really get to be ourselves.

2271
02:37:10,680 --> 02:37:12,640
There's no place like this
out there for us.

2272
02:37:12,920 --> 02:37:14,240
That's true.

2273
02:37:14,720 --> 02:37:17,200
I'm not allowed
to teach junior and seniors.

2274
02:37:17,320 --> 02:37:18,240
You're not allowed?

2275
02:37:20,200 --> 02:37:23,680
Ms. G, we can fight this, you know,
like the Freedom Riders.

2276
02:37:23,800 --> 02:37:25,480
Yeah, yeah,
we'll all drive around on a bus.

2277
02:37:25,560 --> 02:37:27,480
Only this time, they try and bust us up,

2278
02:37:27,600 --> 02:37:29,320
We bust a few of them
board members' heads.

2279
02:37:29,920 --> 02:37:30,880
Marcus.

2280
02:37:31,000 --> 02:37:34,480
Or we can go to the newspapers,
media. That'll get their attention.

2281
02:37:34,680 --> 02:37:36,120
Or we can paint
the administration building

2282
02:37:36,240 --> 02:37:38,600
With the word "assholes"
in various colors.

2283
02:37:40,280 --> 02:37:41,880
Hey, it's something. We can do this.

2284
02:37:47,120 --> 02:37:48,040
What?

2285
02:37:48,120 --> 02:37:51,560
These are my books, not Scott's.
I'm packing the wrong books.

2286
02:37:51,640 --> 02:37:53,280
Honey, take a break.

2287
02:37:57,080 --> 02:37:58,480
Sit down.

2288
02:38:01,520 --> 02:38:04,000
I can't believe I'm getting divorced.

2289
02:38:05,400 --> 02:38:07,760
I never thought this would happen.

2290
02:38:11,560 --> 02:38:13,560
What do I do now?

2291
02:38:14,520 --> 02:38:16,880
Next year, I won't even have my kids.

2292
02:38:17,240 --> 02:38:19,440
You think you should stay with them?

2293
02:38:20,280 --> 02:38:22,480
Or is it better they move on?

2294
02:38:22,840 --> 02:38:24,240
I don't know.

2295
02:38:27,880 --> 02:38:30,240
It's just a job, like you said.

2296
02:38:30,360 --> 02:38:31,920
Yeah, it is.

2297
02:38:32,800 --> 02:38:34,680
But is the job finished?

2298
02:38:36,920 --> 02:38:38,480
Listen to me now.

2299
02:38:38,720 --> 02:38:41,160
What you've done with those kids...

2300
02:38:43,480 --> 02:38:45,680
I don't even have words for it.

2301
02:38:47,320 --> 02:38:52,080
But one thing's for sure,
you are an amazing teacher.

2302
02:38:53,880 --> 02:38:55,200
Special.

2303
02:38:55,960 --> 02:39:00,160
You have been blessed with a burden,
my daughter.

2304
02:39:02,040 --> 02:39:03,960
And I envy you that.

2305
02:39:06,520 --> 02:39:08,080
And I admire you.

2306
02:39:10,520 --> 02:39:14,320
And how many fathers ever get
to say that to their daughters

2307
02:39:14,480 --> 02:39:16,360
And really mean it?

2308
02:39:20,080 --> 02:39:23,040
What she is suggesting
is in violation of our union charter.

2309
02:39:23,160 --> 02:39:26,160
She may not move on with her students
to teach them junior year.

2310
02:39:26,280 --> 02:39:28,200
She's only been here two years.

2311
02:39:28,280 --> 02:39:30,320
There are teachers here
who have tenure,

2312
02:39:30,400 --> 02:39:32,560
Who have worked and committed
themselves for far longer

2313
02:39:32,680 --> 02:39:34,520
To attain a position of seniority.

2314
02:39:34,600 --> 02:39:38,400
Not to mention their experience
in teaching students of a higher caliber.

2315
02:39:38,520 --> 02:39:41,200
The Distinguished Scholars Program
is under our jurisdiction.

2316
02:39:41,360 --> 02:39:44,000
I don't want to replace
the Distinguished Scholars Program.

2317
02:39:44,120 --> 02:39:45,960
I just want to stay
with my kids next year.

2318
02:39:46,040 --> 02:39:48,160
She can't. I have the juniors.

2319
02:39:48,240 --> 02:39:50,160
The Board of Education
will not allow this.

2320
02:39:50,320 --> 02:39:52,160
Teaching rotations will be disrupted,

2321
02:39:52,280 --> 02:39:54,480
Retirement schedules
will be reevaluated,

2322
02:39:54,560 --> 02:39:57,880
Disrespecting teachers
who have earned their way far longer

2323
02:39:57,960 --> 02:40:00,040
And who focus on the classroom,

2324
02:40:00,120 --> 02:40:02,840
Not on public relations
and newspaper articles.

2325
02:40:02,960 --> 02:40:04,840
I didn't ask for those articles
to be written.

2326
02:40:04,960 --> 02:40:06,400
She's in the middle of a divorce.

2327
02:40:06,520 --> 02:40:08,880
Note, they stay late in her class,
they're eating, they're playing games!

2328
02:40:09,000 --> 02:40:11,960
All right, let's all just take a breath here.
All right?

2329
02:40:13,360 --> 02:40:15,360
Now I had hoped
that we could talk this out,

2330
02:40:15,480 --> 02:40:17,120
Maybe come to some kind
of arrangement.

2331
02:40:17,240 --> 02:40:19,640
- There is no arrangement...
- Margaret.

2332
02:40:20,440 --> 02:40:21,880
Carl, look.

2333
02:40:22,440 --> 02:40:25,360
Putting aside all obvious resentments
for the moment,

2334
02:40:25,480 --> 02:40:26,800
Even if an arrangement were made

2335
02:40:26,920 --> 02:40:30,880
And she could teach them as juniors,
there isn't an accredited course

2336
02:40:31,000 --> 02:40:33,240
In the curriculum for her to teach.

2337
02:40:33,880 --> 02:40:37,360
Unless Brian trades one of his
junior classes for a sophomore.

2338
02:40:37,480 --> 02:40:38,480
No.

2339
02:40:40,200 --> 02:40:42,320
Then there's nothing I can do.

2340
02:40:45,720 --> 02:40:46,960
So that's it?

2341
02:40:48,080 --> 02:40:49,480
Believe it or not, Ms. Gruwell,

2342
02:40:49,560 --> 02:40:52,200
There are other capable teachers
in this school.

2343
02:40:52,320 --> 02:40:54,240
If you've made the progress
you say you have,

2344
02:40:54,360 --> 02:40:55,960
Your students should be ready
to move on.

2345
02:40:56,080 --> 02:40:58,640
They might even gain something
from more experienced teachers.

2346
02:40:58,720 --> 02:41:01,840
You can't teach them.
You don't even like them.

2347
02:41:01,960 --> 02:41:03,720
What does that have to do
with teaching?

2348
02:41:03,800 --> 02:41:06,320
I've been an educator for over 30 years.

2349
02:41:06,680 --> 02:41:08,320
I have students that still remain
in touch with me.

2350
02:41:08,440 --> 02:41:10,760
I know what it is to be loved
by a classroom!

2351
02:41:10,840 --> 02:41:13,720
You have no idea
how many battles I've had

2352
02:41:13,800 --> 02:41:15,400
Fighting to be a better teacher,

2353
02:41:15,480 --> 02:41:18,720
And now, what, suddenly I'm incapable
of educating your students?

2354
02:41:18,840 --> 02:41:21,360
You know, if they move on
to our classes and they fail,

2355
02:41:21,520 --> 02:41:23,480
It'll be because they weren't prepared!

2356
02:41:23,640 --> 02:41:26,200
Lt'll be because you failed, not them!

2357
02:41:44,040 --> 02:41:46,600
Andre? Wait a minute before you go in.

2358
02:41:59,320 --> 02:42:01,680
I heard about your brother's conviction.
I'm sorry.

2359
02:42:01,800 --> 02:42:03,920
Is that why you've missed class
so much?

2360
02:42:04,000 --> 02:42:05,720
I had things to do.

2361
02:42:08,880 --> 02:42:10,600
About this.

2362
02:42:11,040 --> 02:42:12,160
The evaluation assignment

2363
02:42:12,280 --> 02:42:13,680
Was to grade yourself
on the work you're doing.

2364
02:42:13,760 --> 02:42:16,120
You gave yourself an F.
What's that about?

2365
02:42:16,480 --> 02:42:19,560
- It's what I feel I deserve. That's all.
- Oh, really?

2366
02:42:21,080 --> 02:42:22,680
You know what this is?

2367
02:42:23,000 --> 02:42:26,800
This is a "Fuck you" to me,
and everyone in this class!

2368
02:42:26,960 --> 02:42:30,080
I don't want excuses.
I know what you're up against.

2369
02:42:30,400 --> 02:42:32,560
We're all of us up against something.

2370
02:42:33,480 --> 02:42:36,720
So you better make up your mind,
because until you have the balls

2371
02:42:36,800 --> 02:42:39,480
To look me straight in the eye
and tell me this is all you deserve,

2372
02:42:39,600 --> 02:42:41,080
I am not letting you fail,

2373
02:42:41,120 --> 02:42:43,120
Even if that means coming
to your house every night

2374
02:42:43,200 --> 02:42:44,840
Until you finish the work.

2375
02:42:44,920 --> 02:42:46,640
I see who you are.

2376
02:42:47,160 --> 02:42:49,200
Do you understand me?

2377
02:42:50,200 --> 02:42:52,080
I can see you.

2378
02:42:53,880 --> 02:42:55,720
And you are not failing.

2379
02:42:59,000 --> 02:43:03,760
So, take a minute.
Pull yourself together and come inside.

2380
02:43:04,280 --> 02:43:06,200
I want a new evaluation.

2381
02:43:11,200 --> 02:43:13,880
An F. What, are you tripping?

2382
02:43:19,320 --> 02:43:22,640
I want you all to know that
Dr. Cohn and I tried very hard.

2383
02:43:25,320 --> 02:43:28,080
But it's been decided we can't continue
with each other junior year.

2384
02:43:28,200 --> 02:43:29,240
- What?
- What?

2385
02:43:30,840 --> 02:43:32,640
You... Wait.

2386
02:43:33,360 --> 02:43:35,240
Wait. Guys. Everyone.

2387
02:43:36,600 --> 02:43:38,960
No! That don't fly, Ma!

2388
02:43:40,440 --> 02:43:43,960
Look, first of all,
I'm not anyone's mother in here, okay?

2389
02:43:44,080 --> 02:43:46,160
No, it doesn't mean mother.

2390
02:43:46,840 --> 02:43:49,080
It's a sign of respect for you.

2391
02:44:02,720 --> 02:44:04,080
Listen to me.

2392
02:44:04,280 --> 02:44:05,520
All of you.

2393
02:44:06,280 --> 02:44:10,720
Don't use me as another excuse
for why you can't make it.

2394
02:44:12,560 --> 02:44:15,720
You made it to your junior year.

2395
02:44:16,480 --> 02:44:19,160
Think about how you did that.

2396
02:44:20,480 --> 02:44:24,000
Everyone in this room
has a chance to graduate.

2397
02:44:25,000 --> 02:44:27,440
For some,
you'll be the first in your family.

2398
02:44:27,560 --> 02:44:30,200
The first with a choice to go to college.

2399
02:44:31,160 --> 02:44:33,840
Some may move faster than others.

2400
02:44:35,400 --> 02:44:37,600
But you'll each have the chance.

2401
02:44:38,640 --> 02:44:41,480
And you did that. Not me.

2402
02:44:48,280 --> 02:44:51,760
Now, I have one

2403
02:44:53,720 --> 02:44:55,280
Final project in mind.

2404
02:44:55,360 --> 02:44:57,480
- Ms. G.
- Yeah?

2405
02:44:59,240 --> 02:45:04,000
<i>Ms. G wanted us to put our diaries
together in a book, just like Anne Frank.</i>

2406
02:45:04,720 --> 02:45:06,640
<i>She got this businessman, John Tu,</i>

2407
02:45:06,800 --> 02:45:09,520
<i>to donate 35 computers
so we could work.</i>

2408
02:45:14,360 --> 02:45:17,640
<i>She told us we have something
to say to people.</i>

2409
02:45:17,800 --> 02:45:18,960
<i>We weren't just kids
in a class anymore.</i>

2410
02:45:19,000 --> 02:45:20,080
<i>We weren't just kids
in a class anymore.</i>

2411
02:45:20,200 --> 02:45:23,760
<i>We were writers with our own voices,
our own stories.</i>

2412
02:45:23,840 --> 02:45:25,840
<i>And even if nobody else read it,</i>

2413
02:45:25,920 --> 02:45:29,360
<i>the book would be something
to leave behind that said we were here,</i>

2414
02:45:29,960 --> 02:45:32,920
<i>this is what happened, we mattered.</i>

2415
02:45:33,400 --> 02:45:37,480
<i>Even if it was just to each other.
And we won't forget.</i>

2416
02:45:39,120 --> 02:45:41,360
<i>Ms. G didn't promise
it would get published or anything,</i>

2417
02:45:41,480 --> 02:45:44,240
<i>but we could get it out there ourselves.</i>

2418
02:45:44,920 --> 02:45:47,080
<i>She asked us to come up with a title,</i>

2419
02:45:47,600 --> 02:45:49,480
<i>something to call ourselves.</i>

2420
02:46:06,520 --> 02:46:08,320
I just received a call
from Karin Polacheck

2421
02:46:08,440 --> 02:46:09,520
At the Board of Education.

2422
02:46:09,640 --> 02:46:11,560
There's to be a meeting
with Dr. Cohn about your classes.

2423
02:46:11,680 --> 02:46:15,000
- Do you know anything about this?
- No.

2424
02:46:22,480 --> 02:46:27,720
These students, this class,
they've become a family.

2425
02:46:28,600 --> 02:46:30,120
To who? To you?

2426
02:46:30,760 --> 02:46:32,320
To each other.

2427
02:46:33,080 --> 02:46:36,280
Room 203 is a kind of a home for them.

2428
02:46:36,800 --> 02:46:40,000
Their trust is all wrapped up
in us being together as a group.

2429
02:46:40,440 --> 02:46:41,520
Once they're out of her class,

2430
02:46:41,640 --> 02:46:43,960
Believe me they'll slip back
into their old habits.

2431
02:46:44,080 --> 02:46:47,880
Their reading scores, their writing
has markedly improved, Ms. Campbell.

2432
02:46:48,000 --> 02:46:51,360
On paper. But what has
she accomplished in reality?

2433
02:46:51,480 --> 02:46:53,040
What about new students
that come in next year?

2434
02:46:53,120 --> 02:46:55,040
Can she repeat
this process every year?

2435
02:46:55,160 --> 02:46:56,480
Her methods are impractical,

2436
02:46:56,600 --> 02:46:59,120
Impossible to implement with regularity.

2437
02:46:59,200 --> 02:47:01,600
What if every teacher
performed in this way?

2438
02:47:02,200 --> 02:47:03,360
We have millions of children

2439
02:47:03,480 --> 02:47:05,120
To get through the education system
in this country,

2440
02:47:05,240 --> 02:47:06,960
And we need a means
of accomplishing that

2441
02:47:07,080 --> 02:47:09,840
Which allows as many students
to benefit as possible,

2442
02:47:09,960 --> 02:47:11,800
Not just special cases.

2443
02:47:13,240 --> 02:47:16,560
And you honestly think you can create
this family in every classroom,

2444
02:47:16,720 --> 02:47:19,560
For every grade,
for every student you teach?

2445
02:47:23,960 --> 02:47:25,360
I don't know.

2446
02:47:31,320 --> 02:47:32,560
Thank you.

2447
02:47:52,120 --> 02:47:54,920
Hey, there go Ms. G.
Hey, there go Ms. G!

2448
02:48:03,480 --> 02:48:04,800
What happened?

2449
02:48:05,560 --> 02:48:09,200
So? Are we gonna be together
for junior year?

2450
02:48:14,840 --> 02:48:16,080
No.

2451
02:48:16,960 --> 02:48:18,760
- What?
- What?

2452
02:48:23,160 --> 02:48:26,400
We're gonna be together junior
and senior year.

2453
02:48:27,800 --> 02:48:28,800
Yes!

